he Logic-Forum for solutions of this challenge." /><span>Solutions</span></a></td><td class="done">done&nbsp;<a href="/challengestats.php?challengeid=200" title="695 users have solved this challenge so far.">[695]</a></td></tr></table></td></tr></table></div><div class="challenge_div">Logic made by inferno !thx!<p class="challenge_1" style="text-align:center;">
Here you see several equations. As you might have noticed, these equations aren't correct.
<br />
Your task is to make them correct, by removing three symbols from the equation, and add those three symbols to your solution.
<br />
F.e. 13 + 4 = 6*7<br />
3 + 4 = 7<br />
1, 6 &amp; * are removed.<br />
This means the solution now is "16*".<br />
It is also possible to remove any +,- or * symbol.<br /><br />

Here is your task:<br /><br />

1. 132 * 16 = 11 - 3 + 7 * 9<br />
2. 19 + 45 = 39 * (4 + 16)  <br />
3. 13 + 214 = 3 * 3 * 14 * 6<br />
4. 3 * (7+26) = 3 * 40 + 9  <br />
5. 17 + 143 - 7 = 28 - 3 * 5<br />
<br />

